LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 889
Introduced by Clouse, 37.
Read first time January 08, 2026
Committee: Judiciary
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the State Electrical Act; to amend section
2 81-2143, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska; to change a penalty;
3 and to repeal the original section.
4 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB889 LB889
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 81-2143, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 81-2143 It shall be a Class IV felony to I misdemeanor knowingly and
4 willfully to commit or to order, instruct, or direct another to commit
5 any of the following acts:
6 (1) To make a false statement in any license application, request
7 for inspection, certificate, or other lawfully authorized or required
8 form or statement provided by the State Electrical Act;
9 (2) To perform electrical work for another without a proper license
10 for such work;
11 (3) To fail to file a request for inspection when required;
12 (4) To interfere with or refuse entry to an inspector lawfully
13 engaged in the performance of his or her duties; or
14 (5) To fail or neglect to comply with the act or any lawful rule,
15 regulation, or order of the board.
16 Sec. 2. Original section 81-2143, Reissue Revised Statutes of
17 Nebraska, is repealed.
